issue.title: [CF 772] Monochrome Font Outline Crashes Game
issue.body:
IMPORTANT: If your issue is only occurring with a specific icon, include an export string of the icon in this ticket. Subsequently, if the issue involves an entire group or an entire profile, include the entire export string of the group or profile.

To get an export string, open the icon editor, and click button labeled "Import/Export/Backup". Select the "To string" option for the appropriate export type (icon, group, or profile), and then press CTRL+C to copy it to your clipboard.

FAILURE TO COMPLY WITH THE ABOVE INSTRUCTIONS WILL RESULT IN YOUR TICKET BEING INVALIDATED.

What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. Clone Default: Icon Layout 1.
2. Switch to cloned layout and select stacks.
3. Attempt to change font outline to monochrome.

What do you expect to happen? What happens instead?
I expect the font outline to switch to monochrome. Error 132 fatal exception, memory could not be read at such and such address.

What version of TellMeWhen are you using? ("The latest" is not a version)

Does this issue happen repeatedly if you keep trying to change the font outline to monochrome? I ask because I am completely unable to reproduce this error.

The crash report itself doesn't actually indicate a problem with TMW, which leads me to believe that it may be some issue with drivers or hardware or something else:

``` Current Addon: (null) Current Addon function: UNKNOWN Current Addon object: (null) ```

It is extremely uncommon for an addon action to trigger an error 132 unless there is some deeper issue at hand - WoW's Lua environment is designed with a specific goal that addons shouldn't be able to cause the whole game to crash.

I'm afraid there just isn't anything I can do about this crash. Have you tried running in DX11 mode? That is really the only thing that I can think of - it might be a bug with hardware acceleration for monochrome font rending that might be fixed if you try running WoW in DX11 mode.
